# Phoenix .gitignore
#
# The repo is source-available under a non-commercial license, but every
# user runs it against their own brokerage data. NOTHING that holds personal
# trade history, authentication material, or cloud credentials should ever
# end up on GitHub. This file is the safety net for "I accidentally git add'd
# a sensitive thing".
#
# Sections, in order of how-bad-if-leaked:
#   1. Auth + cloud credentials  (immediate compromise)
#   2. User data                 (trade history, broker statements, logs)
#   3. Local databases           (any *.db / *.sqlite at the project root)
#   4. Personal notes            (scratch files, TODOs, request lists)
#   5. Build / cache artefacts   (annoying-but-harmless)
#   6. Editor / OS junk          (cosmetic)
#   7. P&L recovery audit trail  (specific to this repo's history)


# ============================================================================
# 1. AUTH + CLOUD CREDENTIALS — leaking any of these is catastrophic.
# ============================================================================

# Real env files (auth hash, Flask SECRET_KEY, IBKR tokens). The .example
# template is the ONLY env file that ships.
.env
.env.*
!.env.runtime.example

# Generic credential / secret file names commonly created during dev.
*.token
*_token
*.credentials
.credentials
.secrets
secrets.json
secrets.yml
secrets.yaml
secrets.toml

# Cloud provider credentials. Never commit these even if you're certain
# they're scoped/expired — leaked tokens get harvested in minutes.
.aws/
aws-credentials
aws.env
.gcp/
gcp-key*.json
service-account*.json
.azure/

# SSH / GPG / TLS material.
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
*.cer
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.*
id_dsa
*.gpg
*.asc
*.kdbx


# ============================================================================
# 2. USER DATA — trade history, raw IBKR exports, run logs.
#    All gitignored even when they live inside the project tree.
# ============================================================================

# Raw broker statements (XML from Flex Web Service, CSV from Activity Statement).
downloaded/

# App + ingest logs. Tokens are now redacted at the source, but the log file
# still contains trade history, account IDs, IPs, and timing. Keep out of git.
logs/

# Docker-mode user data directory. Holds data.db, downloaded/, logs/ inside
# when running via docker compose. Bind-mounted from the host.
phoenix-data/


# ============================================================================
# 3. LOCAL DATABASES — any *.db / *.sqlite is presumed to hold trade data.
# ============================================================================

# The canonical Phoenix DB (and SQLite's WAL / journal sidecars).
data.db
data.db-journal
data.db-wal
data.db-shm

# Catch-all for ad-hoc SQLite files dropped at the project root.
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3


# ============================================================================
# 4. PERSONAL NOTES — author's scratch files, request lists, local TODOs.
# ============================================================================

requested.txt
notes.local.md
notes-*.md
TODO.local.md
TODO.local.txt
scratch.*
scratch/


# ============================================================================
# 5. BUILD / CACHE / TEST ARTEFACTS — regenerable, no value in version control.
# ============================================================================

# Python bytecode and caches
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Distribution / packaging
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg
pip-wheel-metadata/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# Test + lint caches
.pytest_cache/
.tox/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pyre/

# Coverage
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
coverage.xml

# Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints/


# ============================================================================
# 6. EDITOR / OS JUNK
# ============================================================================

# Editors
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~

# Backups / temporaries created by Claude or editors
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig
*.tmp.*

# Claude Code artefacts (assistant session metadata, never useful in repo)
.claude/

# OS-level
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Local Docker compose overrides (often used for dev-only mounts/ports)
docker-compose.override.yml
docker-compose.override.yaml
docker-compose.local.yml
docker-compose.local.yaml


# ============================================================================
# 7. P&L RECOVERY AUDIT TRAIL
# ============================================================================
# After the 2026-04-25 truncation incident, reports/pnl.py was rebuilt from
# scratch and verified output-identical to these reference artefacts. They
# live on disk as a personal audit trail but should NEVER ship in the repo.
# Paths exist for both the pre- and post-src/-restructure layouts.
reports/_pnl_legacy.pyc
reports/_pnl_decompiled_reference.txt
src/reports/_pnl_legacy.pyc
src/reports/_pnl_decompiled_reference.txt
